00:41:11.200 --> 00:41:15.380
by management and culture
than it was in the past.

00:41:15.380 --> 00:41:17.780
I think it's terribly
important for value investors

00:41:17.780 --> 00:41:20.690
to recognize that a key
source of investment success

00:41:20.690 --> 00:41:23.760
is to become long-term
passive partners

00:41:23.760 --> 00:41:26.610
with extraordinary human
beings who many would

00:41:26.610 --> 00:41:29.230
regard as freaks or misfits.

00:41:29.230 --> 00:41:32.490
When George Bernard Shaw said
that "the reasonable man adapts

00:41:32.490 --> 00:41:35.450
himself to the world;
the unreasonable one

00:41:35.450 --> 00:41:38.040
persists in trying to
adapt the world to himself.

00:41:38.040 --> 00:41:41.580
Therefore all progress depends
on the unreasonable man,"

00:41:41.580 --> 00:41:45.300
was he talking about
freaks and misfits?

00:41:45.300 --> 00:41:48.470
Shouldn't the label of freak
and misfit not sometimes

00:41:48.470 --> 00:41:51.550
be relabeled as
intelligent fanatics?

00:41:51.550 --> 00:41:54.350
That's what this bias is
about, the representativeness

00:41:54.350 --> 00:41:56.330
heuristic, labels.

00:41:56.330 --> 00:41:57.740
We apply labels.

00:41:57.740 --> 00:42:00.430
And a label of a
freak and misfit,

00:42:00.430 --> 00:42:02.590
which is a negative
connotation, can easily

00:42:02.590 --> 00:42:06.960
be sometimes relabeled as
an intelligent fanatic.

00:42:06.960 --> 00:42:09.860
And it makes all the difference.

00:42:09.860 --> 00:42:11.960
One of my key learnings
from studying such people

00:42:11.960 --> 00:42:15.010
is that, as an investor, I have
to teach myself to overlook

00:42:15.010 --> 00:42:17.580
many of their personality
traits, some of which

00:42:17.580 --> 00:42:19.490
are not admirable at all.

00:42:19.490 --> 00:42:22.080
Indeed, I think those
traits are a consequence

00:42:22.080 --> 00:42:24.516
of their fanatic
focus on their work.

00:42:24.516 --> 00:42:26.140
I have been consciously
training myself

00:42:26.140 --> 00:42:29.530
to empathize with such
extraordinary human beings.

00:42:33.550 --> 00:42:35.920
In his wonderful book
"The Social Animal,"

00:42:35.920 --> 00:42:39.860
Elliot Aronson talks about the
insidious nature of prejudice.

00:42:39.860 --> 00:42:43.250
He quotes a fictional
dialogue from Gordon Allport's

00:42:43.250 --> 00:42:45.270
classic book "The
Nature of Prejudice."

00:42:45.270 --> 00:42:47.380
I think the dialogue
is worth reading.

00:42:47.380 --> 00:42:50.210
Mr. X says that "the
trouble with Jews

00:42:50.210 --> 00:42:52.610
is that they only take
care of their own group."

00:42:52.610 --> 00:42:56.250
Mr. Y, who's the prejudiced
person, says-- sorry,

00:42:56.250 --> 00:42:57.560
Mr. X is the prejudiced person.

00:42:57.560 --> 00:43:00.340
Mr. Y is the interrogator.

00:43:00.340 --> 00:43:03.080
He says, "But the record of
the Community Chest campaign

00:43:03.080 --> 00:43:05.030
shows that they give
more generously,

00:43:05.030 --> 00:43:07.530
in proportion to their numbers,
to the general charities

00:43:07.530 --> 00:43:10.120
of the community
than do non-Jews."

00:43:10.120 --> 00:43:12.740
Mr. X then responds,
"That shows they're always

00:43:12.740 --> 00:43:15.680
trying to buy favor and
intrude into Christian affairs.

00:43:15.680 --> 00:43:17.300
They think of nothing but money.

00:43:17.300 --> 00:43:19.840
And that's why there are
so many Jewish bankers."

00:43:19.840 --> 00:43:22.280
Mr. Y responds,
"But a recent study

00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:25.280
shows that the percentage of
Jews in the banking business

00:43:25.280 --> 00:43:28.530
is negligible, far smaller than
the percentage of non-Jews."

00:43:28.530 --> 00:43:31.160
Mr. X then responds,
"That's just it.

00:43:31.160 --> 00:43:33.314
They don't go in for
respectable businesses.

00:43:33.314 --> 00:43:34.730
They're only in
the movie business

00:43:34.730 --> 00:43:37.880
or they run nightclubs."

00:43:37.880 --> 00:43:40.280
The dialogue illustrates
the insidious nature

00:43:40.280 --> 00:43:43.520
of prejudice far better than
the mountain of definitions.

00:43:43.520 --> 00:43:46.070
In effect, the prejudiced
Mr. X is saying,

00:43:46.070 --> 00:43:47.450
don't trouble me with the facts.

00:43:47.450 --> 00:43:49.210
My mind is made up.

00:43:49.210 --> 00:43:51.270
He makes no attempt to
dispute the data presented

00:43:51.270 --> 00:43:54.220
by Mr. Y. He either
distorts the facts in order

00:43:54.220 --> 00:43:56.030
to make them support
his hatred of Jews

00:43:56.030 --> 00:43:58.860
or he bounces off
them, undaunted,

00:43:58.860 --> 00:44:03.510
to a new area of attack.

00:44:03.510 --> 00:44:05.460
A deeply prejudiced
person is virtually

00:44:05.460 --> 00:44:07.290
immune to information
at variance

00:44:07.290 --> 00:44:10.060
with his or her
cherished stereotypes.

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:14.120
As famed jurist Oliver
Wendell Holmes, Jr. once said,

00:44:14.120 --> 00:44:18.730
"Trying to educate a bigot
is like shining light

00:44:18.730 --> 00:44:22.790
into the pupil of an
eye-- it constricts."

00:44:22.790 --> 00:44:26.460
Whlie Aronson's words, that
a deeply prejudiced person

00:44:26.460 --> 00:44:29.080
is virtually immune to
information at variance

00:44:29.080 --> 00:44:31.600
with his or her
cherished stereotypes,

00:44:31.600 --> 00:44:34.110
apply to many
prejudiced human beings,

00:44:34.110 --> 00:44:37.310
they do apply, if you think
about it, to Mr. Market.

00:44:37.310 --> 00:44:40.600
That's because Mr. Market
is a learning machine.

00:44:40.600 --> 00:44:43.700
He corrects his
prejudices over time.

00:44:43.700 --> 00:44:45.960
While the five patterns
of prejudice that I just

00:44:45.960 --> 00:44:51.190
outlined they keep coming
back in one form or the other,

00:44:51.190 --> 00:44:54.150
the prejudice against
specific examples

00:44:54.150 --> 00:44:57.610
conforming to these patterns
tends to disappear over time.

00:44:57.610 --> 00:45:01.420
We have a name for that,
and we call that rerating.

00:45:01.420 --> 00:45:03.710
I think there are
two lessons here.

00:45:03.710 --> 00:45:06.340
The first one I've
already told you about.

00:45:06.340 --> 00:45:08.470
The second one is that
we should look at Mr.

00:45:08.470 --> 00:45:10.120
Market with some respect.

00:45:10.120 --> 00:45:14.700
After all, he's far
less prejudiced than us.

00:45:14.700 --> 00:45:18.620
Why couldn't we learn to get rid
of some of our own prejudices

00:45:18.620 --> 00:45:20.400
from him.

00:45:20.400 --> 00:45:22.161
Thank you.

